chicken and the egg? In an ideal Otto engine, you don't need a cooling
system. Why not? I have customers with 9.5-11:1 on pump gas (though not in
busses) running cool as a cucumber with stock cooling systems. Run 8.5:1 on
a stock or mild cam and burn it up in 5K miles.

John
Aircooled.Net Inc.

